    "# 37. The Equipment Selection Problem (RTG vs. RMG vs. Straddle)\n",
    "## Tier 1: Multi-Objective Mathematical Optimization with Pareto Optimization\n",
    "\n",
    "### Goal\n",
    "Select optimal container handling equipment (RTG, RMG, or Straddle Carriers) by simultaneously optimizing multiple conflicting objectives: minimizing total cost of ownership, maximizing operational throughput, minimizing environmental impact, and maximizing operational flexibility.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Assumptions\n",
    "- Terminal operates 24/7 with 8 container blocks\n",
    "- Equipment has different capital costs, operating costs, productivity rates, and flexibility indices\n",
    "- Planning horizon of 20 years with 15% discount rate\n",
    "- Single equipment type selection constraint (can't mix types in this simplified model)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Approach (Step-by-Step)\n",
    "1. **Define Equipment Types and Parameters**: RTG, RMG, and Straddle Carriers with their respective costs and capabilities\n",
    "2. **Formulate Multi-Objective Optimization**: Create four objective functions for cost, throughput, stacking capacity, and flexibility\n",
    "3. **Apply Pareto Optimization**: Find non-dominated solutions where no objective can be improved without worsening others\n",
    "4. **Generate Pareto Front**: Enumerate feasible solutions and identify Pareto-optimal configurations\n",
    "5. **Analyze Trade-offs**: Compare solutions across different objectives to support decision-making\n",
    "\n",
    "### What to Look for in the Results\n",
    "- Pareto-optimal solutions that balance cost, efficiency, and flexibility\n",
    "- Trade-off analysis between different equipment types\n",
    "- Cost breakdown showing capital vs. operating expenses\n",
    "- Capacity analysis showing daily throughput capabilities\n",
    "\n",
    "### Concrete Example\n",
    "Mediterranean Container Terminal (MCT) expansion:\n",
    "- 2-block terminal requiring 2,400 moves/day capacity\n",
    "- Budget constraint of \$180 million\n",
    "- Equipment options with different cost and performance characteristics\n",
    "\n",
    "### Why this Tier Exists vs Other Approaches\n",
    "**Mathematical optimization provides:**\n",
    "- **Optimality guarantees**: Finds provably optimal solutions within the defined model\n",
    "- **Transparent trade-offs**: Clear quantification of objective conflicts and compromises\n",
    "- **Reproducible results**: Same inputs always produce the same optimal solutions\n",
    "- **Foundation for comparison**: Establishes benchmark for heuristic and metaheuristic methods\n",
    "\n",
    "**Limitations that motivate higher tiers:**\n",
    "- Computational complexity grows exponentially with problem size\n",
    "- Requires precise parameter values (sensitive to uncertainty)\n",
    "- Limited ability to handle complex constraint interactions\n",
    "- Static analysis doesn't capture dynamic operational realities"
   ]
  },
