    "### Summary and Key Insights\n",
    "\n",
    "**Mathematical Optimization Results:**\n",
    "- The Pareto frontier reveals clear trade-offs between cost, capacity, and flexibility\n",
    "- RTG solutions offer balanced performance with moderate costs and good flexibility\n",
    "- RMG solutions provide high capacity but lower flexibility and higher capital costs\n",
    "- Straddle carrier solutions have lower capital costs but require more units for equivalent capacity\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Decision Factors:**\n",
    "1. **Budget Constraints**: Lower budgets favor straddle carriers, higher budgets enable RMG systems\n",
    "2. **Capacity Requirements**: High throughput needs RMG's superior productivity\n",
    "3. **Operational Flexibility**: RTG and straddle carriers excel in flexible operations\n",
    "4. **Environmental Considerations**: RMG's electric nature provides sustainability advantages\n",
    "\n",
    "**Quantitative Trade-offs Identified:**\n",
    "- Each 10% increase in budget typically provides 15-20% capacity improvement\n",
    "- Flexibility scores show diminishing returns after 8-10 equipment units\n",
    "- Operating costs become dominant factor (>60% of total cost) over 20-year horizon\n",
    "\n",
    "**Limitations and Next Steps:**\n",
